SIMPLE: untoward
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untoward
<hw>Un*to"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Unto</ets>
+ <ets>-ward</ets>.]</ety> <def>Toward.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untoward</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Untoward
<hw>Un*to"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>toward</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Froward; perverse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Save yourselves from
this <xex>untoward</xex> generation.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Acts ii.
40.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Awkward; ungraceful.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Untoward</xex> words.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Creech.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Untoward</xex> manner.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Swift.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Inconvenient; troublesome; vexatious; unlucky;
unfortunate; <as>as, an <ex>untoward</ex> wind or
accident</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*to"ward*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*to"ward*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untowardly</ent>⟦br⟧
